                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d142">
                <head>No. 142.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Morton</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-10-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 1, 1883</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 359.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to previous correspondence
                    concerning the international conference for the protection of submarine cables,
                    and particularly with reference to the telegram of the Department of the 21st
                    ultimo, authorizing you and Mr. Vignaud to attend the cable conferences and
                    conclude the convention, I now inclose herewith the necessary full powers in the
                    premises.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>[Incloses full powers, as above.]</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
